								</script></div>{% endfor %}{% endpaginate %}{% assign product = defaultProduct %}</div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-1da7bcbe" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-361da7bc pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-c6defcf0" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-79c6defc"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-d6da2caa"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-00d6da2c">Anti-Inflammatory Support Multi-Vitamin</span></h3><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-cdb1d511" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-4a05c823"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d11d8946">Turmeric</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-c82392e3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d9a34600">Curcumin</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-92e36927"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-b2fbd3a5">Boswellia</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-6927cdb1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-7f1d4a05">Ginger Root</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-3fe3302d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-fed03fe3">Quercetin</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-5d219f12"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-655e5d21">Rutin</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-391ddaaf"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-f1e5391d">Bromelain</span></li></ul><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-aa4e7179"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-2caa4e71">The ingredients listed above are all proven to be excellent for countering inflammation and other joint problems. Each one of them has added health benefits. For example, turmeric is an antioxidant and works to ward off the symptoms of depression and arthritis, while bromelain helps with inflammation and digestion. Quercetin is especially good for the blood vessels of your heart and can be used to fight off infections.    </span></p><a href="/products/anti-inflammatory-support-90-capsules" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-e6f657b0"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-7179c6de">Learn more about Anti-Inflammatory Support Multi-Vitamin</span></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-a474bcfa" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-fba474bc"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-f0868009"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-fcf08680">SAMe </span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-099f2bfb"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-80099f2b">S-adenosyl-L-methionine (SAMe) is a natural compound that helps regulate the body's hormones while also strengthening cell membranes. Synthetic versions are used in supplements, and they can help lower pain levels associated with arthritis while simultaneously increasing the functionality of the joints. It is also useful for treating fibromyalgia, anxiety, depression, chronic pain, and fatigue.     </span></p><a href="/products/sam-e-400mg-elemental-sam-e" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-7694d9de"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-2bfba474">Learn more about SAMe</span></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-c5d45a53" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-39c5d45a"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-fa0ea053"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bcfa0ea0">Glucosamine</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-53d33b39"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a053d33b">Glucosamine is an amino sugar. It is found in the cartilage between bones. Supplements with this compound are used for treating a number of pain-related issues such as arthritis, chronic back pain, multiple sclerosis, and jaw pain. There are quite a few skin creams that feature glucosamine for its pain-relieving properties.      </span></p><a href="/products/glucosamine-chondroitin-msm-90-capsules" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-69210cd3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-3b39c5d4">Learn more about Glucosamine</span></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-2dc0340e" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-a92dc034"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-53daa254"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5a53daa2">Chondroitin</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-54ca7ba9"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a254ca7b">This natural sulfate is found within the cartilage between joints. It is the primary cause of elasticity within cartilage due to the water retaining properties it possesses. It has the ability to slow some of the enzymes that lead to breakdowns in cartilage. It is often used in supplements with Glucosamine, which can relieve pain. Some other benefits of chondroitin include assisting in the treatment of cataracts, muscle soreness, heart disorders, psoriasis, and kidney infections.      </span></p><a href="/products/glucosamine-chondroitin-msm-90-capsules" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-90b7ab2e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-7ba92dc0">Learn more about Chondroitin</span></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-eb56e515" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-52eb56e5"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-0e6b9a6c"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-340e6b9a">MSM</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-6c00ed52"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-9a6c00ed">Methylsulfonylmethane (MSM) is a compound containing sulfur that is known by several names, including "methyl sulfone" and "dimethyl sulfone." MSM is able to assist the body in a number of ways, such as improving skin, lowering incidents of allergy symptoms, and decreasing both joint pain and inflammation. MSM is also used in hair growth treatments for disorders like alopecia.      </span></p><a href="/products/msm-methylsulfonylmethane-1000mg-90-capsules" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-f0ae5725"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-ed52eb56">Learn more about MSM</span></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-08361da7" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-4e08361d"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-15b83972"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-e515b839">Vitamin D3</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-724f224e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-39724f22">This vitamin is a fat-soluble secosteroid that helps with the absorption of certain substances like phosphate, calcium, and magnesium for distribution throughout the body. Vitamin D3 is responsible for maintaining strong and healthy bones. It has other benefits when included with a dietary supplement, including boosting your immune system and lowering the chances of developing either osteoporosis or osteomalacia.       </span></p><a href="https://wholehealth.com/products/vitamin-d3-extra-strength-2000-iu-60-capsules" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-81729138"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-224e0836">Learn more about Vitamin D3</span></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-1db8fa54" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-b98b1db8"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-425730ec"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-cb22577b">Vitamin K2</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-30ec0819"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-ab88801b">The Vitamin K group is fat-soluble and is mostly centered around providing nutrients to support bone and blood health. It is also responsible for creating essential blood clotting factors. Vitamin K2, in particular, is found in leafy vegetables, fish, and eggs. This supplement can help boost your metabolism and ensure you can absorb enough calcium to keep your bones and teeth strong.        </span></p><a href="https://wholehealth.com/collections/bone-joint-health/products/nowr-vitamin-k-2-100mcg" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-0819b98b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-60894257">Learn more about Vitamin K2</span></a></div><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-03f7371e"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-f124e0bf"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-34f32237">Cal-Mag</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-e0bff7fc"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8d7f7f5d">This supplement is meant for men and women to make sure that they get the right amount of Vitamin D, calcium, and magnesium each day. It keeps the musculoskeletal system healthy and also benefits the nervous system and heart.        </span></p><a href="/products/cal-mag-calcium-magnesium-citrates-1400mg-120-capsules" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-f7fc03f7"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bff3f124">Learn more about Cal Mag</span></a></div><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-c5641722"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-7b2936b1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-373da2eb">Fish Oil</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-36b10990"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-2a805201">Fish oil has a large number of health advantages of taken regularly. It contains omega-3 fatty acids, which are also excellent for aiding in repairing ligament injuries, as well as Vitamins A and D. They can work in the following ways.        </span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-20955c4e" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-433cccc2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-690160af">Protects against heart disease</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-ccc2dafe"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-75351441">Can be used to help treat specific mental issues such as bipolar disorder and schizophrenia</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-dafee40b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-90c9146a">Aids in weight loss</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-e40b2095"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8cc4433c">Reduces the likelihood of vision loss due to aging</span></li></ul><a href="/products/extra-strength-omega3-fish-oil-high-epadha-90-softgels" target="_self" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-pZdvY kuwSuz pf-0990c564"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6cde7b29">Learn more about Fish Oil</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-43b19969" id="4" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-e3aeb1a0 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--6"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-c6e3aeb1" id="" data-pf-type="Column"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-bee53866"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bcbee538">Get Rid of Inflammation in Your Body</span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-66482648"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-38664826">Stress management, routine exercise, and lowering your sugar intake can help to rid the body of inflammation. Eating healthy and taking supplements to ensure that your body gets all the vitamins it needs will also ensure that your joints stay pain-free so that you can move comfortably.&nbsp;<br></span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-48aeb733"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-2648aeb7">Dietary Guide For Joint Health</span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-339bc76d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-b7339bc7">Several important dietary staples that have vitamins that will help combat joint and bone deterioration include fish, nuts, whole grains, various fruits, and dairy products. The fatty acids in fish and naturally occurring vitamins in the other foods all have benefits that can increase your overall health while also targeting joint discomfort. <br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--6"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-310177fc" data-pf-type="Column"></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-c91e6679" id="5" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-d9dfc91e pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-2bc0d9df" id="" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-e7f32bc0"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-9ee03dab"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-b9c350bb">Do Vitamins For Joints Really Work?</span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-fa7ce48a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8af6fa7c">It is a well known scientific fact that vitamins are vital to bone and joint health. There are many studies from all over the world about various vitamin supplements and how they interact with joints, bone, and cartilage. Some have mixed results, while others have too few participants to make any concrete discoveries. Every supplement provided in the sections below have data backing up their efficacy. 
<br>
<br>While the field can always benefit from more research, we do have a pretty big body to work with already. Below are several studies that have proven the positive benefits of specific vitamins on joint health.&nbsp;<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-e388e7f3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-e38d9ee0">A 2015 study conducted in China showed conclusive proof that both glucosamine and chondroitin successfully treated knee joint pain. <br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-6193e2f5"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-983d6193">A 2001 study by the University of Miami confirmed that ginger root extract had a mild positive effect on individuals suffering from osteoarthritis.<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-59fe7b2e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-582359fe">A 2016 meta-analysis out of South Korea confirmed that turmeric helps decrease joint pain experienced by people with arthritis.<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-3dab364a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-e9d8f5ed">Those are several of a large body of scientific work that positively connects vitamin supplements with healthier bones and joints.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-45d45f56" id="6" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-0245d45f pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-7f9d7481" id="" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-557f9d74"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-9b415707"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-949b4157">F.A.Q- Frequently Asked Questions</span></h2><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-07557f9d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5707557f">For anyone new to taking supplements and vitamins, it might be a bit confusing trying to figure out exactly which ones you need or how to determine what could potentially be the cause of your joint discomfort. Below are common questions. You can find out more about specific supplements by checking out their page in our online catalog.       </span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-8039327f" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-bc803932"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-818a6067"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-74818a60">Does B12 deficiency cause joint pain?</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-67bc8039"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6067bc80">The short answer is yes. Vitamin B12 is responsible for metabolism within the body's cells, and it keeps blood cells and nerves working properly. A deficiency can lead to nerve damage and anemia. Some of the most common side effects of not having enough B12 in your diet include the following.      </span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-9f2e5ce1" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-51427b1d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4b9d552b">Tingling sensations in arms and legs</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-7b1dfc48"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0b1b4b6b">Decreased count of red blood cells</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-fc48979d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-f5546ef8">Mood disorders such as anxiety, depression, or irritability</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-979d25fc"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-e483dc27">Issues with vision</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-25fc7c85"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d41559f8">Problems with balance or locomotion</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-7c859f2e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a76f5142">Joint pain</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-67200f57" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-cc67200f"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-7f52d7a5"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-327f52d7">How does a Vitamin D deficiency affect joint pain?</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-a5cc6720"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d7a5cc67">A 2017 Swedish study was able to link Vitamin D supplements with overall pain management. It is also known that a Vitamin D deficiency can cause joint pain, so making sure that you have enough in your diet or included in your supplements can help.<br></span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-770428bc" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-ed770428"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-57ccf957"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0f57ccf9">Who should not take glucosamine?</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-57ed7704"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-f957ed77">There are certain individuals who will want to avoid taking glucosamine or supplements that feature it as a compound. Anyone with a shellfish allergy should avoid supplements with glucosamine sulfate because it is often sourced from shellfish. There are forms that are made in a laboratory that would not affect an allergy sufferer. It is best to speak with a health professional before taking glucosamine if you have the following conditions which may be affected by it.      </span></p><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-42986e34" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-380fcd12"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-02dab303">Diabetes</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-cd12f042"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-ad96ff61">High blood pressure</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-f042853b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4fed0cca">Kidney disease</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-853b4298"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-ec7d380f">Any bleeding-related disorders</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-06d69566"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4b3306d6">Problems with balance or locomotion</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-a31259de"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8f35a312">Heart disease</span></li></ul><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-5fb57054"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0cbd5fb5">If you are on blood thinners, then you will want to avoid both chondroitin and glucosamine. It is known to have an effect on glucose levels and certain cholesterols. It should not be taken by people who eat a diet that is abnormally high in fatty food as it might increase the risk of high cholesterol and related disorders.       </span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-f22f8986" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-a0f22f89"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-bc72daf8"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-28bc72da">Are bananas bad for arthritis?</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-f8a0f22f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-daf8a0f2">Men with prostate cancer can benefit from heart healthy foods like oatmeal. This food is also a good source of antioxidants. It can improve blood pressure, cholesterol, blood sugar levels, and oatmeal can help with weight loss goals      </span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-bd2dd895" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-e2bd2dd8"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-861e6975"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-89861e69">What are the side effects of living without a prostate? </span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-75e2bd2d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6975e2bd">They are actually perfect for various forms of arthritis and treating joint issues. Bananas have significant levels of potassium and magnesium. They both are excellent nutrients for increasing bone density. Magnesium is known to alleviate joint pain caused by arthritis. Bananas are known to help stop inflammation, strengthen the immune system of cells, and they are excellent antioxidants.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-f553a10f" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-08f553a1"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-951026fa"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d8951026">Can glucosamine cause liver damage?</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-fa08f553"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-26fa08f5">In 2018 the National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases ran a study to determine if glucosamine causes liver damage. They found no evidence that regular use of glucosamine causes liver damage. They determined that it would be under exceptionally rare circumstances if it took place, which might be due to the quality of glucosamine or other conditions.&nbsp;<br><br>The study went on to note that even in cases where it appeared that taking a glucosamine supplement caused liver problems, there was no way to determine if it was, instead, due to some contaminant that may have been mixed into a low-quality supplement. They had no reason to believe that an amino sugar would cause mild or severe liver damage based on the known data.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-c8684982" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-07c86849"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-dc18977b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-c184dc18">Does glucosamine make you gain weight?</span></h3><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-ad07c868"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-18ad07c8">The diet that you eat is going to determine whether glucosamine will support weight loss or weight gain. As was mentioned in an earlier question, glucosamine is an amino sugar, and it does sometimes cause a rise in blood sugar, which might lead to very slight weight gain. However, a 2015 Korean study showed that glucosamine could contribute to weight loss when combined with a high-fat diet. For diets with high amounts of carbs and low-fat foods, it can cause weight gain. 
<br>
<br>In either case, the difference is minimal, and faster weight loss is more likely to occur when combined with regular exercise.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-ca2e4745 pf-lg--hidden pf-md--hidden pf-sm--hidden pf-xs--hidden" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-63ca2e47 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-6463ca2e" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-oUbqx bgMQOP pf-e26463ca"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-566ee019"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5f566ee0">Article Sources</span></h3><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-5638959b" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4630875/" data-target="_blank" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-1966410e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-e0196641">Kava Kava for anxiety</span></li><li data-href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25732379/" data-target="_blank" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-0ece14ad"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-410ece14">Omega-3 fatty acids and stress</span></li><li data-href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK507250/" data-target="_blank" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-ad1c5e06"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-14ad1c5e">Magnesium and stress</span></li><li data-href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/10401554/" data-target="_blank" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-06e26463"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5e06e264">Influence of S-adenosyl on chronic stress</span></li></ul></div></di